<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9804> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9804" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/16> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 223" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8951> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8951" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 740" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6983> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6983" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He very probably governed a province after his consulship, for he was convicted of res repetundae (Val. Max 6.9.10 refers wrongly to a Lex Caecilia repetundarum, which is usually taken as a mistake for the Lex Calpurnia; see Mommsen, GS 1.16-17; Strafrecht 708, note 3, 729, note 1; and cf. Cic. Brut. 106; Off. 2.75; Festus 360L-285M; Lucilius, 20.607-608, in LCL). But see C. Busacca, Iura 19, 1968, 83-93, who holds that the Lex Caecilia set up a quaestio extraordinaria, through which Lentulus was convicted of res repetundae ca. 154, but which did not involve, like the Lex Calpurnia, the creation of a quaestio perpetua. M. G. Morgan holds, against Zippel and De Sanctis, that Lupus was not the Cornelius mentioned by Polybius (frag. 64 B-W; see Walbank, Comm. Polybius III, p. 748, ad loc.; App. Illyr. 14) who was defeated by the Pannonians, nor the commander who suffered a disaster at the hands of the Scordisci (Historia 23, 1974, 183-216). Xvir s. f. The L. Cornelius Lentulus who in 140 raised the question of bringing an aqueduct to the Capitolium, though termed a praetor in RE nos. 190192, was one of the Xviri s. f. and was acting for the college (Frontin. Aq. 1.7, accepting Schone's emendation pro collegio; cf. Liv. OXy. Per. 54), and may best be identified with the consul of 156 (Sumner, Orators 48). The notices on L. Cornelius Lentulus, Pr. 140, in MRR 1.479, and of any connection with the consul of 130 should be deleted.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3070> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3070" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Raised the question of bringing an aqueduct to the Capitol contrary to the Sibylline oracles (Frontin. Aq. 1.7; cf. Liv. Oxy. Per. 54).{480}" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3033> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3033" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Bardt (Priester 30) accepts the emendation collegio in Frontin. Aq. 1.7 (see above, Praetors, and note 1), identifies Lepidus and Lentulus as above, and because of the mention of the Sibylline Oracles lists them as Decemviri." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2967> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2967" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 124, 464f.; Fast. Ant., ib. 160f. Cornelius was elected in spite his previous conviction under the Lex Caecilia (Val. Max. 6.9.10; Fest. 360 L; see 154, on Caecilius Metellus). P. Cornelius Scipio Nasica Corculum was probably chosen Princeps Senatus (Diod. 34-35.33.6; Val. Max. 7.5.2; cf. Plut. Aem. 15.2; see Willems, Sénat 1.113, note 3)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2873> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2873" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Brut. 79; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 50f., 123f., 462f.; Fast. Ant., ib. 160f.; Obseq. 16; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Marcius, Val. Max. 9.3.2. Marcius received command in Dalmatia where, after initial reverses, he captured several towns and besieged Delminium (Liv. Per. 47; Flor. 2.25; App. Illyr. 11; Obseq. 16; cf. Polyb. 32.14.2, who mentions commissioners that were sent to Illyria with Marcius)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2864> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2864" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Reported a decree of the Senate to the People of Tibur (CIL 1\n     .2.586- ILS 19). This Cornelius is generally identified with Lupus the Consul of 156, and so must have held the praetorship by 159." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2845> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2845" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "After Demetrius' escape to Syria, these were appointed to examine the condition of Greece; and in Asia, to observe the result of Demetrius' action, the attitude of the other kings, and to settle their disputes with the Galatians (Polyb. 31.15.9-12, and 32-33; Diod. 31.28)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2830> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2830" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Didasc. Ter. Heaut. Tim. On Valerius, see Münzer, Gent. Val. 40, no. 18." .
